<%- include('../partials/navbar') %>
  <main class="main-content">
    <div class="top-header"><span class="header-title">Program Scope</span>
      <div class="header-right"><a href="/program/submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-sm">+ Submit Report</a>
        <% if (locals.user) { %><a href="/profile/<%= user.id %>" class="header-user"><div class="header-avatar"><%= ((user.first_name||user.username).charAt(0)).toUpperCase() %></div></a><% } %>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="page-body">
      <div class="breadcrumb"><a href="/program">Bug Bounty</a><span>›</span><span>Scope</span></div>

      <div class="grid-2" style="align-items:start;gap:24px;">
        <div>
          <div class="card mb-4">
            <div class="card-header" style="background:#F0FDF4;"><h3 style="color:#15803D;">✓ In-Scope Assets</h3></div>
            <div class="table-wrapper">
              <table>
                <thead><tr><th>Asset</th><th>Type</th><th>Coverage</th></tr></thead>
                <tbody>
                  <% [
                    {a:'syntex.local',t:'Web App','c':'Full — all features, all endpoints'},
                    {a:'api.syntex.local',t:'API',c:'REST API v1 + v2, all methods'},
                    {a:'admin.syntex.local',t:'Admin Panel',c:'Full — including bypass testing'},
                    {a:'staging.syntex.local',t:'Staging',c:'All features — may have extra vulns'},
                    {a:'dev.syntex.local',t:'Development',c:'All features — verbose errors'},
                    {a:'*.syntex.local',t:'Wildcard',c:'Any unlisted subdomain'},
                    {a:'localhost:3000',t:'Direct',c:'Direct app access (bypass nginx)'},
                    {a:'localhost:5432',t:'Database',c:'PostgreSQL — if reachable via SSRF'},
                  ].forEach(r => { %>
                  <tr>
                    <td><code style="font-size:12px;"><%= r.a %></code></td>
                    <td><span class="badge badge-info" style="font-size:10px;"><%= r.t %></span></td>
                    <td style="font-size:12px;"><%= r.c %></td>
                  </tr>
                  <% }) %>
                </tbody>
              </table>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="card mb-4">
            <div class="card-header" style="background:#FEF2F2;"><h3 style="color:#B91C1C;">✗ Out-of-Scope</h3></div>
            <div class="card-body" style="font-size:13px;">
              <% [
                {item:'mail.syntex.local',why:'Email infrastructure — not part of the web app'},
                {item:'vpn.syntex.local',why:'VPN gateway — out of testing scope'},
                {item:'backup.syntex.local',why:'Backup service — dead in this lab'},
                {item:'DoS / DDoS',why:'Any availability attack — zero tolerance'},
                {item:'Social engineering',why:'No phishing of other lab users'},
                {item:'Physical security',why:'Not in scope for this lab'},
                {item:'Third-party services',why:'Stripe, AWS, etc. are not our assets'},
                {item:'Automated scanning without PoC',why:'Tool output ≠ a valid report'},
              ].forEach(r => { %>
              <div style="display:flex;gap:10px;padding:8px 0;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-light);">
                <span style="color:var(--danger);font-weight:700;flex-shrink:0;">✗</span>
                <div><strong style="font-size:12px;"><%= r.item %></strong><div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text-muted);"><%= r.why %></div></div>
              </div>
              <% }) %>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <div class="card mb-4">
            <div class="card-header"><h3>Valid vs Invalid Reports</h3></div>
            <div class="card-body" style="font-size:13px;">
              <p style="font-weight:700;color:var(--success);margin-bottom:8px;">✓ Valid Examples</p>
              <% [
                'SQL injection in /login that bypasses authentication',
                'Stored XSS in comments that fires in admin\'s browser',
                'IDOR on /orders/:id exposing other users\' PII',
                'SSRF via /api/v1/fetch reaching internal services',
                '/.env accessible without authentication (credentials exposed)',
                'JWT alg:none accepted — forge any user token',
              ].forEach(e => { %><div style="display:flex;gap:8px;margin-bottom:6px;"><span style="color:var(--success);">•</span><span><%= e %></span></div><% }) %>

              <p style="font-weight:700;color:var(--danger);margin-top:16px;margin-bottom:8px;">✗ Invalid / Won't Fix</p>
              <% [
                'Missing security headers (CSP, HSTS) — informative only',
                '"User can see their own data" — not a vulnerability',
                'Self-XSS (only affects yourself)',
                'Rate limit on non-sensitive endpoints',
                'SSL/TLS configuration issues on lab environment',
                'Clickjacking on non-sensitive pages',
              ].forEach(e => { %><div style="display:flex;gap:8px;margin-bottom:6px;"><span style="color:var(--danger);">•</span><span><%= e %></span></div><% }) %>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="card mb-4">
            <div class="card-header"><h3>Rules of Engagement</h3></div>
            <div class="card-body" style="font-size:13px;line-height:1.8;">
              <ol style="padding-left:20px;">
                <li>Test only against this local lab instance.</li>
                <li>Do not attempt to access other users' real data outside the lab.</li>
                <li>Do not run automated scanners against production systems.</li>
                <li>Report vulnerabilities before discussing them publicly.</li>
                <li>Do not perform destructive actions (drop tables, delete users).</li>
                <li>One report per unique vulnerability — do not spam variants.</li>
                <li>Good faith testing is always respected here.</li>
              </ol>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-header"><h3>Duplicate Report Policy</h3></div>
            <div class="card-body" style="font-size:13px;line-height:1.7;">
              <p>If your report is marked <strong>Duplicate</strong>, it means someone else reported the same vulnerability first. The original reporter receives credit and bounty.</p>
              <p style="margin-top:8px;">A duplicate report is still useful — it confirms the severity and adds context. Duplicates are always acknowledged and the reporter is added to the <a href="/program/hall-of-fame" style="color:var(--accent);">Hall of Fame</a> if this is their first finding.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</div>
<%- include('../partials/footer') %>
